A new enum class, mx.accessibility.AccConst, now centralizes, makes public, and documents all the ROLE_XXX, STATE_XXX, and EVENT_XXX constants defined by Microsoft's Active Accessibility (MSAA) specification.

These constants are for use in writing AccessibilityImplementation subclasses. With this checkin, only the AccImpl base class has been converted to use them, but soon all of its subclasses will be converted as well.
Doc notes: We need to get ALL accessibility classes showing up in ASDoc, both in the Player and in Flex.
